# New style strikes
Rabbit Punch					KEY:Unchained Style Strike ~ Rabbit Punch			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Style Strike.SpecialQuality	DESC:The monk gives a sharp blow to the back of a foe's head. The critical threat range and critical multiplier of this strike increase by 1, and the monk gains a +2 bonus on attack rolls to confirm a critical hit with this strike. This increase is not doubled by Improved Critical or similar effects. Creatures without a discernible head are unaffected by this style strike (subject to GM discretion). The monk must attack with a fist to use this style strike.																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.6
Throat Crush					KEY:Unchained Style Strike ~ Throat Crush			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Style Strike.SpecialQuality	DESC:The monk gives a sharp blow to a foe's throat, hampering its ability to speak for 1 round as if it had the caster croak spellblight (Pathfinder RPG Ultimate Magic 95) . Creatures without a discernible throat, or with multiple vocal organs, are unaffected (subject to GM discretion).																																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Break							KEY:Unchained Style Strike ~ Break					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Style Strike.SpecialQuality	DESC:The monk combines a writhing twist with a violent strike against a foe that is grappling him. If the monk's attack is successful, he can attempt a grapple combat maneuver check or Escape Artist check as a free action to escape a grapple, adding the strike's damage as a bonus on his check.																																																																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.7

# New Unchained Monk Ki Powers
Action Before Thought			KEY:Unchained Ki Power ~ Action Before Thought		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Ki Power.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Action Before Thought										PREVARGTEQ:KiPowerLVL,6																								DESC:A monk with this ability can spend 2 ki points as a free action as part of rolling initiative to roll twice on the initiative check and take the higher result. A monk must be at least 6th level before selecting this ki power.																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Bare-Hand Block					KEY:Unchained Ki Power ~ Bare-Hand Block			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Ki Power.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Bare-Hand Block											PREVARGTEQ:KiPowerLVL,8			PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Ki Sunder										DESC:A monk with this ability can spend 1 ki point as an immediate action when attacked with a manufactured weapon to attempt an unarmed sunder combat maneuver check against it. If he successfully sunders the weapon and grants it the broken condition, the attack deals no damage. He can spend an additional 1 ki point when using this ability to activate ki sunder as a free action. A monk must be at least 8th level and have the ki sunder ki power before selecting this ki power.																				SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Breaking-Down Koan				KEY:Unchained Ki Power ~ Breaking-Down Koan			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Ki Power.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.Breaking-Down Koan											PREVARGTEQ:KiPowerLVL,8																								DESC:A monk with this ability can spend 1 ki point as a swift action to present a paradox, riddle, or complicated question to a creature within 30 feet. The creature must succeed at a Will save (DC %1) or be confused for 1 round. This is a mind-affecting, language-dependent effect. A monk must be at least 8th level before selecting this ki power.|10+(MonkLVL/2)+WIS																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Building-Up Koan				KEY:Unchained Ki Power ~ Building-Up Koan			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Ki Power.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.Building-Up Koan											PREVARGTEQ:KiPowerLVL,8																								DESC:A monk with this ability can spend 2 ki points as a swift action to ask himself a koan, which he then tries to answer. The monk must attempt a Will save (DCÂ %1). If successful, he gains an insight bonus equal to his Wisdom modifier to AC and on attack rolls, saving throws, skill checks and until the end of the round. If he fails, the monk is instead confused for 1 round. This is a mind-affecting, language-dependent effect. A character who can't become confused can't benefit from this ability. A monk must be at least 8th level before selecting this ki power.|15+(MonkLVL/2)	SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Ki Sunder						KEY:Unchained Ki Power ~ Ki Sunder					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Ki Power.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Ki Sunder																																										DESC:A monk with this ability can spend 1 ki point as a free action when attempting a sunder combat maneuver check to add his monk level as a bonus to the damage roll.																																																																																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Master-Thought Koan				KEY:Unchained Ki Power ~ Master-Thought Koan		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Unchained Ki Power.SpecialQuality.Supernatural.Master-Thought Koan											PREVARGTEQ:KiPowerLVL,12		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Breaking-Down Koan,Building-Up Koan			DESC:A monk with this ability can spend an additional 2 ki points when using either the breaking-down koan or building-up koan ki powers. When combined with master-thought koan, breaking-down koan affects a number of characters of your choice within 30 feet equal to the monk's wisdom modifier. When combined with master-thought koan, building-up koan can be used on an ally within 30 feet. A monk must be at least 12th level and have either the breaking-down koan or the building-up koan ki power before selecting this ki power.							SOURCEPAGE:p.20
